Below is a clean, QA-friendly list of commonly used JavascriptExecutor.executeScript() commands in Selenium, including scrolling, clicking, input, highlighting, and page info.


üîπ Basic Syntax

JavascriptExecutor js = (JavascriptExecutor) driver;
js.executeScript("javascript_code", arguments);


üìú Scrolling Scripts (MOST USED)


Scroll element into view

js.executeScript("arguments[0].scrollIntoView(true);", element);


Scroll to bottom of page

js.executeScript("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);");


Scroll to top of page

js.executeScript("window.scrollTo(0, 0);");


Scroll by pixels

js.executeScript("window.scrollBy(0, 500);");


Smooth scroll

js.executeScript("arguments[0].scrollIntoView({behavior: 'smooth'});", element);


üñ± Click & Input Scripts


Click element (when normal click fails)

js.executeScript("arguments[0].click();", element);


Set value in input field

js.executeScript("arguments[0].value='test value';", element);


Clear input field

js.executeScript("arguments[0].value='';", element);


‚ú® Element Styling / Highlighting (DEBUGGING)


Highlight element

js.executeScript(
  "arguments[0].style.border='3px solid red';", element
);


Change background color

js.executeScript(
  "arguments[0].style.background='yellow';", element
);


üìè Page & Element Info


Get page title

String title = (String) js.executeScript("return document.title;");


Get current URL

String url = (String) js.executeScript("return window.location.href;");


Get element text

String text = (String) js.executeScript("return arguments[0].innerText;", element);


Get attribute

String cls = (String) js.executeScript("return arguments[0].getAttribute('class');", element);


‚è± Page Load & Ready State


Check page load complete

String state = (String) js.executeScript("return document.readyState;");


Expected:

complete


üö´ Disable / Enable Elements


Disable element

js.executeScript("arguments[0].setAttribute('disabled','true');", element);


Enable element

js.executeScript("arguments[0].removeAttribute('disabled');", element);


üßπ Remove Element (for testing)

js.executeScript("arguments[0].remove();", element);


ü™ü Browser & Alert


Refresh page

js.executeScript("location.reload();");


Trigger alert

js.executeScript("alert('Test Alert');");


üß™ Scroll inside div (VERY USEFUL)

js.executeScript(
  "arguments[0].scrollTop = arguments[0].scrollHeight;", element
);


üó£ Interview One-Liner


JavascriptExecutor is used in Selenium to perform actions like scrolling, clicking, and interacting with hidden or non-responsive elements when standard WebDriver methods fail.

